column2: Algae bloom seems to be over and there is very little rain.
Algae bloom in shallow portion of lake.
Partly cloudy- small amount of algae.
Cloudy- algae growth is high- water is dirty.
Clear sky- some algae- down a lot from last month.  Water no longer brown.
Cloudy- water remains brown- very little algae.
Clear- windy- warm ~80 degrees - very clear water.
Mostly cloudy- east wind- cool- no algae.
Clear- SW wind- small amount algal bloom.  Clear water best I've ever seen.  Beautiful.
Hot- water level down- water + clear + warm.
Windy- east wind- overcast- wind has agitated the lake.
Clear warm- algal bloom in progress.
Hot + sunny- algae growth on surface.
Hot + windy- water is brown- improving- runoff from rain
Sunny- clam- SW wind lake more clear than ever seen.
Cloudy- water high- 4" of rain the previous week.
Windy- rain- last several days- partly cloudy.
Cool- cloudy- algae bloom in progress.
Hot with surface water temp at 86 degrees in shade
clear water; apparent algae on lake bottom
clear mid-lake but algae clumps on northeast end
Surface Algae 50-70 feet solid from north shore
Lots of algae northeast side: 50-60 feet from shore; floating
Surface algae on northeast side; very green throughout lake
Majority of lake clear; northeast side = heavy algae close to shore
Thunderstorms and windy last few days - lake "stirred up"
Recent heavy rain; lake very green with algae
Lots of rain; lake level a little higher
